@startuml Data Channel Creation Sequence

title Data Channel Creation - Detailed Sequence Flow

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 200

actor "User" as User
participant "Mini App\n(Vue.js)" as MiniApp
participant "DSBridge" as DSBridge
participant "JSApi" as JSApi
participant "JsEventDispatcherFactory" as Factory
participant "DCJsEventDispatcher" as DCDispatcher
participant "DCMiniUseCase" as DCUseCase
participant "MiniAppManager" as AppMgr
participant "DCManager" as DCMgr
participant "DCServiceManager" as DCService
participant "Terminal AIDL\n(IImsDataChannel)" as AIDL
participant "5G Modem" as Modem
participant "IMS Network" as Network
participant "Remote Party" as Remote

== Phase 1: User Interaction ==

User -> MiniApp : Click "Create Data Channel"
activate MiniApp

MiniApp -> MiniApp : Prepare DC Parameters\n(dcLabels, DataChannelAppInfoXml)

note right of MiniApp
  dcLabels format:
  "local_[appId]_[index]_[label]"
  Example: "local_333_1_test"

  DataChannelAppInfoXml contains:
  - StreamId
  - Direction (sendrecv/sendonly/recvonly)
  - Priority
  - MaxBitrate
  - Other DC parameters
end note

== Phase 2: JavaScript to Native Bridge ==

MiniApp -> DSBridge : dsbridge.call('async', {\n  event: 'dc',\n  function: 'createAppDataChannel',\n  params: {...}\n}, callback)
activate DSBridge

DSBridge -> JSApi : async(msg, handler)
activate JSApi

JSApi -> JSApi : Parse JSON to JSRequest\nevent='dc'\nfunction='createAppDataChannel'\nparams={dcLabels, DataChannelAppInfoXml}

== Phase 3: Event Routing ==

JSApi -> Factory : getEventDispatcher('dc')
activate Factory

Factory -> Factory : Create/Get DCJsEventDispatcher
Factory --> JSApi : DCJsEventDispatcher instance
deactivate Factory

JSApi -> DCDispatcher : dispatchAsyncMessage(request, handler)
activate DCDispatcher

DCDispatcher -> DCDispatcher : Route to createAppDataChannel()

== Phase 4: Validation & Processing ==

DCDispatcher -> DCUseCase : createAppDataChannel(request, handler)
activate DCUseCase

DCUseCase -> DCUseCase : Validate Parameters
note right of DCUseCase
  Validation checks:
  1. dcLabels contain correct appId
  2. Labels not already created
  3. DataChannelAppInfoXml valid XML
  4. Insert StreamId if missing
end note

DCUseCase -> DCUseCase : Parse DataChannelAppInfoXml

DCUseCase -> AppMgr : createDC(dcLabels, description)
activate AppMgr

== Phase 5: DC Manager Processing ==

AppMgr -> DCMgr : createApplicationDataChannels(\n  dcLabels, description, slotId,\n  callId, remoteNumber)
activate DCMgr

DCMgr -> DCMgr : Create CreateAdcParams object
DCMgr -> DCMgr : Add to createAdcQueue

note right of DCMgr
  Queue contains:
  - slotId
  - callId
  - remoteNumber
  - dcLabels (array)
  - description (XML string)
  - listener callback
end note

== Phase 6: Queue Processing (Background Coroutine) ==

DCMgr -> DCMgr : startCreateADCQueue()\n[Background Coroutine]

loop For each queued request
    DCMgr -> DCMgr : Poll createAdcQueue
    DCMgr -> DCMgr : Check mAdcMap cache

    alt DC exists in cache (OPEN/CONNECTING)
        DCMgr -> AppMgr : onDataChannelCreated()\n[Cached DC]
        note right of DCMgr
          Reuse existing DC
          if still OPEN or CONNECTING
        end note
    else DC not cached or CLOSED
        DCMgr -> DCMgr : Prepare new DC creation
        DCMgr -> DCMgr : Delay 3 seconds\n(rate limiting)

        == Phase 7: AIDL Call to Terminal ==

        DCMgr -> DCService : createImsDc(\n  labels, description,\n  slotId, callId, remoteNumber)
        activate DCService

        DCService -> AIDL : IImsDataChannelServiceController\n.createApplicationDataChannel(\n  labels, description)
        activate AIDL

        == Phase 8: Modem Processing ==

        AIDL -> Modem : Create Data Channels
        activate Modem

        Modem -> Modem : Parse DataChannelAppInfoXml
        Modem -> Modem : Validate parameters

        Modem -> Network : SIP INVITE/UPDATE\n(DC negotiation via SDP)
        activate Network

        Network -> Remote : Negotiate DC creation
        activate Remote

        Remote --> Network : Accept/Reject DC
        deactivate Remote

        Network --> Modem : DC Creation Response
        deactivate Network

        Modem -> Modem : Establish WebRTC\nData Channel

        == Phase 9: Callback from Modem ==

        Modem -> AIDL : onApplicationDataChannelResponse(\n  IImsDataChannel dc)
        deactivate Modem

        note right of AIDL
          DC object contains:
          - dcLabel
          - streamId
          - state (OPEN/CONNECTING/CLOSED)
          - send() method
          - close() method
        end note

        AIDL -> DCMgr : ImsDcCallback\n.onApplicationDataChannelResponse(dc)
        deactivate AIDL
        deactivate DCService

        == Phase 10: DC Caching & Routing ==

        DCMgr -> DCMgr : Cache DC in mAdcMap\nkey = callId + dcLabel

        DCMgr -> DCMgr : Extract appId from dcLabel

        DCMgr -> DCMgr : Determine DC type\n(Own ADC / Control ADC / Regular ADC)

        DCMgr -> AppMgr : onDataChannelCreated(\n  callId, streamId, dc)
        deactivate DCMgr

        == Phase 11: Mini App Notification ==

        AppMgr -> AppMgr : Store DC reference
        deactivate AppMgr

    end
end

== Phase 12: Response to JavaScript ==

DCUseCase -> DCUseCase : Build JSResponse\n{code: "0", msg: "dc1", data: ""}
DCUseCase -> DCDispatcher : handler.complete(response)
deactivate DCUseCase

DCDispatcher --> JSApi : Response
deactivate DCDispatcher

JSApi --> DSBridge : Response
deactivate JSApi

DSBridge -> MiniApp : callback(response)
deactivate DSBridge

== Phase 13: DC Ready for Use ==

MiniApp -> MiniApp : Update UI\n"DC Created Successfully"
MiniApp -> User : Display success message
deactivate MiniApp

note over MiniApp
  Mini App can now:
  - sendData(dcId, data)
  - Register onReceive listener
  - closeAppDataChannel(dcId)
end note

@enduml
